Love it and would highly recommend A*****

reviews.review_text:
A fabulous oasis we stumbled upon unexpectedly, whilst walking the Cotswold Way!!
Stayed a bit too long - and ate a lot!
Started with smoothies from the coffee van, then had sourdough pizzas.
We chose a fabulous big bowl of delicious mixed salads to take with us on the trail for supper that night, and of course we had to take some pastries from the Bolangerie.
Highly recommended!!
reviews.business_response_text: Great to hear you had a good time! We look forward to seeing you soon.

text.en: Great to hear you had a good time! We look forward to seeing you soon.

reviews.review_text: A trendy bar outlet area and cafe for the cider makers. Check out a fabulous range of ciders, supporting acts, real ales, beers gin and tonics, etc. Even a glass of bubbly.  The associated independent food outlets provide a selection of foods from around the globe.  Philippines, Indian asian mixes, burgers and crepes, whatever takes your fancy, set in a stylish rustic setting, good car parking facilities, complete with farm shop and butchery. Don't drive pass, stop and rest or watch the racing or rugby on their large cinema screen.
reviews.business_response_text: Thank you for taking the time to review! We will see you on site soon :-)

I couldnâ€™t give this a good review as I personally found it over crowded and over priced with so little space between the tables inside you had to stand up to let people though. Having experienced my wife out in a wheel chair there is no way this is a wheel chair friendly place as stamped on the google maps summary.

Another review mentioned the same things just three of four weeks ago with poor hygiene standards with no one clearing tables after people have left their dirty plates etc on the table as they left.

All in all a big disappointment and I couldnâ€™t recommend it to anyone or pay another visit to this place.

reviews.review_text: We revisited Dunkertons at the back end of summer, and it was brilliant. It amazes me how far Dunkertons has come as a venue over the last few years, and it is a must-visit. We went as part of a group of two families with children. We started looking around the shop, which has some beautiful produce, including Dunkertons' Organic Cider and a fantastic bakery. We then settled in the courtyard area to eat and drink. It is a fabulous space, which includes welcoming, warm fire-pits, loads of seating and tables. There was loads of selection via the Pop-Up style food court, containing, on our visit, Curry, Pizza, Calamari and Burgers. The bar has an unreal selection for all the family, including fruit juices and a fine selection of beer and traditional, organic Cider. I Love Dunkerton's, and I wish there were a similar place near our home. We will certainly be back and can highly recommend it.
reviews.business_response_text: Thank you very much for such a wonderful review :-)

text.en: Thank you very much for such a wonderful review :-)

reviews.review_text: We went to Dunkertonâ€™s for the first time yesterday and loved it, great food choices and nice atmosphere. We then decided to go back today (26th July) to watch the Lions. Again, great atmosphere and good seats. The one, quite big, downside was The Woozy Pig. It advertised it was doing breakfast until 11am, however, when I queued up at 10.40 to order it, they said they were stopping serving food to get ready for lunch. Considering we travelled there to eat breakfast and watch the Lions, this was extremely disappointing and against what they had advertised. Luckily we managed to get food at the other vendors, but not the same. We will come back but will avoid the Woozy Pig.

reviews.review_text:
Plenty of different food choices to suit everyone and loads of seating. The cider is great too. Dog friendly also which is a bonus.
It would get 5 stars except for the accessibility issues. No designated disabled parking. Drop off in car park onto deep gravel in places which made pushing my walker diffucult. The accessible toilet door was very difficult to close and open so using independently would be difficult. The bin in the loo is right next to the toilet which would make transfering difficult for some it also made reaching the fold down arm much harder. So all in all not accessible for the independent disabled.
reviews.business_response_text: Thank you for taking the time to review Lydia. We look forward to hosting you again soon. There are a limited amount of spaces around the back of the building  still accessible and you are welcome to park there with a Blue Badge. We do not currently have new dedicated Blue Badge spaces in place at the front due to ongoing car park building works, but these will be reinstated as part of the final layout once the works are complete. :-)

reviews.review_text: Very bougie. Myself and a friend spent a Friday night surrounded by the social elite of Cheltenham. Plenty of food & drink options. Everything seemed to be really good quality and to be honest it was nicely priced. We had burgers and cider. No complaints on either from us. If we're in the area I'm sure we'll pop back for another hour of people watching.

In-laws took us here after they had visited a few months ago, it was amazing, great atmosphere , staff were amazing considering how busy they were with the rugby on, Great selection of food , To be honest a bit on the dear side ,but hey great food and you only live once so why not. Shop was really nice , great selection of ciders , we bought 3 cases lol , you could spend all day here , we nearly did . Need a whole sale price  as i could easily sell your ciders in our farm shop in biggleswade. You will see us again.
Andy
